{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"text":": A brand primary color alternative to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"text":" button.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}]},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\", appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Styles","anchor":"Styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pressed"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hovered"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WireframeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Colored surface","anchor":"Colored-surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Specific behavior","anchor":"Specific-behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/48a788-button"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Orange"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text"